Introduction
------------

This piece of software is the real time library for the satellite
emulation testbed OpenSAND used for bloc communications and events
management.

This runtime is a specific implementation.
It is written by Cyrille Gaillardet for Viveris Technologies.

License
-------

see COPYING.LGPL


Library
-------

The sources are in the src subdirectory. The sources build a library
that allow OpenSAND block communications and events management.
See the INSTALL file to learn how to build the libraries.
To compile an application using the OpenSAND ncom library use the
following expression:
gcc `pkg-config opensand_ncom --cflags` `pkg-config opensand_ncom --libs` -o myappli myappli.c


